                <h2>What's New in 2026?</h2>
                <p>
                    The BC PNP landscape for 2026 is dramatically different from
                    previous years. On December 18, 2025, Immigration, Refugees
                    and Citizenship Canada (IRCC) confirmed British Columbia's
                    allocation for the year: <strong>5,254 nominations</strong>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This is a stark contrast to the 9,000 nominations BC
                    requested to meet its labor market needs. While this
                    represents a 31% increase from the <em>initial</em> 4,000 nominations
                    granted in early 2025, it's actually <strong
                        >nearly 1,000 fewer</strong
                    > than the 6,214 nominations BC ultimately received throughout
                    2025 after mid-year top-ups.
                </p>

                <h2>2025 vs 2026: Key Differences</h2>
                <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto my-6">
                    <table class="min-w-full text-left text-sm">
