                <h2>Stream Status for 2026</h2>

                <h3 id="streams">
                    ✅ Skills Immigration (Skilled Worker, ELSS)
                </h3>
                <p>
                    The core Skills Immigration streams remain open. However,
                    with limited allocations, BC PNP is prioritizing candidates
                    with <strong>high economic impact</strong>—meaning higher
                    wages, in-demand occupations, and regional connections
                    matter more than ever. Learn more in our <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-skilled-worker-stream" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Skilled Worker Stream guide</a> or <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-entry-level-semi-skilled" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">ELSS guide</a>.
                </p>

                <h3 id="tech">✅ BC PNP Tech</h3>
                <p>
                    The BC PNP Tech program, which focuses on <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-tech-stream-occupations" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">35 priority
                    technology occupations</a>, is expected to continue operating in
                    2026. Tech candidates typically receive faster processing
                    and weekly draws when the program is active.
                </p>

